critique: This document is an executive order that extends the exemption of James L. Hughes, District Director of Immigration and Naturalization, from compulsory retirement for one year. It cites the authority vested in the president by section 204 of the act of June 30, 1932. There is no clear indication of ideological tilt, immigration approach, executive power implications, federalism concerns, national security vs. civil liberties issues, economic regulation aspects, or social inclusion considerations. The document appears to be an administrative matter concerning a specific individual's employment status.
